In .NET 10, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was removed because Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30+). MAUI now uses **edge-to-edge** display and expects you to react to **window insets** instead.

Here's the modern fix:

### 1. Set `adjustResize` on the Activity

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(Theme = "@style/Maui.MainTheme", /* ... */
          WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

This still tells Android to resize the window — it's the *MAUI wrapper enum* that was removed, not the underlying Android behavior.

### 2. Handle keyboard insets with padding

The edge-to-edge model means your layout now extends behind the keyboard. You need to apply bottom padding when the IME (keyboard) is visible. Add this to `MainActivity`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    AndroidX.Core.View.ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
        Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
}

private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object,
    AndroidX.Core.View.IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(
        Android.Views.View v, AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(
            AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var systemBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(
            AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

        // Use the larger of IME or system bar bottom inset
        int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, systemBarInsets.Bottom);
        v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight, bottomPadding);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

### 3. Layout tip

Make sure your chat input is at the **bottom of a `Grid`**, not in a `ScrollView` footer:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" Placeholder="Type a message..." />
</Grid>
```

The `*` row absorbs the resize, pushing the `Auto`-sized input bar up with the keyboard.

**TL;DR** — The Android-level `adjustResize` still works; you just set it via the `[Activity]` attribute and handle the inset padding yourself since MAUI 10 went edge-to-edge.
